%N A397750 Number of minimum independent dominating sets in the n-path graph.
%H A397750 Andrew Howroyd, <a href="/A397750/b397750.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%H A397750 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/PathGraph.html">Path Graph</a>.
%H A397750 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/IndependentDominatingSet.html">Independent Dominating Set</a>.
%H A397750 <a href="/index/Rec#order_09">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (0,0,3,0,0,-3,0,0,1).
%F A397750 a(3*n) = 1; a(3*n + 1) = binomial(n + 2, 2); a(3*n + 2) = n + 2.
%F A397750 a(n) = 3*a(n-3) - 3*a(n-6) + a(n-9).
%F A397750 G.f.: (1 + x + 2*x^2 - 2*x^3 - 3*x^5 + x^6 + x^8)/((1 - x)*(1 + x + x^2))^3.
%e A397750 a(4) = 3 corresponding to the following independent dominating sets:
%e A397750     x . . x      x . x .     . x . x
%o A397750 (PARI) Vec((1 + x + 2*x^2 - 2*x^3 - 3*x^5 + x^6 + x^8)/((1 - x)*(1 + x + x^2))^3 + O(x^80))
